==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*leǵ-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|necligence}}, {{m|enm|negligence}}, from {{der|en|fro|negligence}}, from {{der|en|la|neglegentia}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈnɛɡlɪd͡ʒəns/}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-negligent.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{hyph|en|neg|li|gence}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# The state of being [[negligent]].
# {{lb|en|legal|singulare tantum}} The [[tort]] whereby a duty of reasonable [[care]] was [[breach]]ed, causing [[damage]]: any conduct short of intentional or [[reckless]] action that falls below the legal standard for preventing unreasonable injury.
# {{lb|en|legal|uncountable}} The breach of a duty of care: the failure to exercise a [[standard of care]] that a [[reasonable person]] would have in a similar situation.

====Usage notes====
* The breach of a duty of care is one element of the tort of negligence, but is also called {{m|en||negligence}}; one must therefore take care to clarify what is meant.

